
Overview of noun spoiler

The noun spoiler has 5 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. spoiler -- (a candidate with no chance of winning but who may draw enough votes to prevent one of the leading candidates from winning)
2. plunderer, pillager, looter, spoiler, despoiler, raider, freebooter -- (someone who takes spoils or plunder (as in war))
3. pamperer, spoiler, coddler, mollycoddler -- (someone who pampers or spoils by excessive indulgence)
4. spoiler -- (an airfoil mounted on the rear of a car to reduce lift at high speeds)
5. spoiler -- (a hinged airfoil on the upper surface of an aircraft wing that is raised to reduce lift and increase drag)
